</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udinadaandedenaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dinadaan DeDenaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/01 2:59:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Changes to what we are proposing to Evade +more.</span><hr size=1> Just responding to your initial news post this thread:<br>
<br>
Evade, sounds cool. Wasnt aware it needed tinkering.<br>
<br>
Bind wounds: Thank @#%$. This to me is a great increase to our playability.<br>
<br>
Pickpockets: Well, ok, but I still think it is a bad idea. Think gems. Think spells. But, I dunno. I think fun as well.<br>
<br>
Specials: Greyed out buttons is a good idea. I agree we need no actual special attacks other than backstab.<br>
<br>
As to poisons: Nonstacking I can live with. Increased drop rates for the highlevel components (heartsting venom, bloodthorn extract, emeraldberry cyanide?) would be nice, especially when they drop off lvl 30plus mobs. I for instance cannot hang around in TT/EJ auctioning for supplies because I will be hunted down and killed, or duped into going to an ambushed trade.<br>
<br>
Further PvP concerns: Please rework mask illusions to where poison and procs will not drop illusion. Mask illusions are fantastic for PvP-teams servers, and when I must use NO poisons or NO illusions, or risk exp death, well, you can see the point I am making I think.<br>
<br>
My last hope is a more general PvP concern that needs looking into IMO. It applies greatly to rogue PvP. When fighting some player (or mob, but the main concern is regarding players), lets say you put him on the run. Now you give chase to him. A rogue ought to really own another player if he is able to keep up with him fleeing. However, unless your connection allows for a constant ping of less than 100, you can be actually hindered by the opponents back (as close as you can possibly get) and still will recieve the 'too far away' message. I know from my own experience that if my opponent moves around I will not be able to engage him in melee until he comes to a complete halt. I also know that this is a big problem for anyone on a dialup service. My ping normally is around 300, in case you are wondering, and in order to hit a runner, I must pass him by a step or two, in which case he is out of my vision anyway. I strongly feel this is a detriment to the game. What I would suggest is simply to increase the melee range for PvP. It certainly doesnt need to be huge like it is for dragons/giants; only an increase of about two steps ought to be enough that the average player can hit a fleeing opponent with melee attack. Alternatively, you could only increase the range of attack from a mob/players back, I have no idea which might be easier to do.<br>
<br>
I will try to go to gameplay discussion and post this there, but I dunno if I can find the ambition. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.13thshadowcompany.com/svimages/new_post.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/01 3:12:10 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/Trinity.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Changes to what we are proposing to Evade +more.</span><hr size=1> "Rogue has earned 10000 hate, top of the hate list.<br>
