<br>
First, we need to post on the original board about these concerns.<br>
<br>
Second, quit shooting the messenger. If you really think Kendrick hasnt got your concerns at heart, you are sadly mistaken. He took the time to come to OUR bouard in order to make sure everyone had the chance to inform themselves of what was being discussed, and to show disrespect or blame for that is pretty crappy.<br>
<br>
Third, I hadnt thought about some of the things which were said here, and the points being made I think have great validity.<br>
<br>
Fourth, I dont care if it makes my survivability less. Too many rogues around now IMO. Let them go back to their old class, lol. I liked rogue pre-evade, and if there are less rogues on big raids that'll suit me fine. The game wasnt designed to have one warrior, 20 rogues, and 2 clerics on a raid. VS wasnt designed to have 2 clerics and 12 wizards on a raid. They way it is getting, the only classes in any guild roster will end up 1 warrior, 1 monk, 1 ranger, 2 paladin, 2 shaman, 5 enchanter, 1 mage, 1 druid, zero sk, 1 necro, 10 cleric, 20 wizard, and 50 rogue. Thats not balance.<br>
<br>
Fifth, if a so-called evade-nerf is implemented, if it helps to increase the viability of other classes by decreasing the viability of multiple rogues, thats great. And thats what we are talking about here, multiple rogues.<br>
 <br>
Sixth, what is evade anyway? Ever read the message you get? It says, ducked out of combat. As in, LEFT COMBAT. As in, stopped attacking! This change will be a BENEFIT for the regular balanced 6 man group. Because it will increase our secondary damage-taking ability. I like it.<br>
<br>
Rogues were fun pre-evade. Rogues were fun post-evade. Rogues will be fun after evade is changed. Maybe more fun since they wont be a dime a dozen anymore. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unluamin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nluamin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/01 3:46:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Changes to what we are proposing to Evade +more.</span><hr size=1> Here is my take of the situation:<br>
<br>
Verant designed the new zones and the uber mobs in Velious and they see that the new zones and the mobs do not provide &quot;enough&quot; challenge to the 1% of the server population.  And remember that Verant thinks that - and I agree here - challenge is needed for a sense of accomplishment and ultimately to keep people playing EQ.<br>
<br>
Well, they look at the uber fights and realize that cleric/warrior/rogue is the group makeup.  Warrior takes the damage, cleric heals the warrior and rogue dishes out the damage and kills the mob.  So they set out to balance the classes.  That's why the hybrids get upgraded and cleric/warrior/rogues get the nerfs.<br>
<br>
Now there is not much we can do if Verant is really intend on balancing the classes in this mind set.  Lets look at some of our suggestions from Verant's point of view:<br>
<br>
1) Make warriors taunt better:  Not gonna happen.  This one beats the purpose of changing the group makeup’s and providing more challenge.<br>
<br>
2) Make evade put rogues in the 10th place: Not gonna happen.  This one makes it possible to have 9 rogues in an epic fight and that's too many.<br>
<br>
<br>
Probable outcome of the &quot;nerf&quot;:<br>
<br>
- Only a limited number of rogues &quot;needed&quot; in the uber fights.<br>
- Decrease in the rogue population.  Most will quit their rogues and some will quit EQ in frustration.<br>
<br>
Now I didn't start my rogue because they were the best damage dealers.  On the contrary, they were considered a broken class and it was hard to find a group looking for a rogue.  Granted, I got used to be the damage dealer and it was certainly ego boosting to see all that damage you made, but I can live with new changes.  I started my rogue because I liked the mind set.  They were hard to play and there were so few of them.  It gave a unique feeling to your character.<br>
Heh, maybe I won't be seeing all those powerleveled rogues anymore.<br>
<br>
<br>
Suggestion:<br>
<br>
- In a 6 person group, I try to stay in the second or third position in the hate list anyway so that I can taunt mobs off casters if the need arises.  Problem here is the lag.  If evade is going to make me number 2, then please make sure that it doesn't fail as much as it does now because of the lag.  Maybe get rid of the &quot;you must stand still&quot; message altogether.  In other words, make it work all the time if hide skill is above a certain level.<br>
<br>
- No matter how you look at it, this change will cap our damage output.  Give us something else in return to make the class more fun, e.g. more traps, better stackable poisons, better implementation of sense and disarm traps, better throwing weapons, more trade skills, more quests or whatever.<br>
<br>
<br>
My 2cp.<br>
<br>
Nluamin<br>
Level 48 Scout of Tunare<br>
Saryrn<br>
